# BACL Multi-Format Extension Audit Preregistry

> **Status: FROZEN 2026-05-18 pre-measurement.** Per `CAMPAIGN_DISCIPLINE.md` Rule 1.1, binding.

## 0. Context

The BACL_subnormal audit ([`../bacl_subnormal_audit/closeout.md`](../bacl_subnormal_audit/closeout.md)) established the unified BACL statement:

> For `a, b ∈ 𝔽⁺` in any IEEE 754 binary format, if `ulp(a) ≥ ulp(b)`, then `a − b = j · ulp(b)` for integer j.

The proof uses only binade-spacing (every float is `N · ulp` for integer N). This mechanism is format-agnostic — only the specific value of `ulp` changes per format.

This audit verifies BACL at multiple IEEE 754 binary formats:
- **float16** (IEEE binary16, half-precision): 11-bit precision, exponent range [−14, +15]
- **float32** (IEEE binary32, single-precision): 24-bit precision, exponent range [−126, +127]
- **float128** (x86 80-bit extended on this platform): 64-bit explicit mantissa, exponent range [−16382, +16383] — **NOT IEEE binary128**; treat as platform-extended format

True IEEE binary128 (128-bit precision, 113-bit mantissa) is not available in standard numpy on this platform. Bfloat16 (8-bit exponent, 7-bit mantissa) requires non-stdlib libraries.

## 1. Per-format BACL parameters (FROZEN)

| Format | Mantissa bits (precision − 1) | emin (smallest normal exp) | smallest_normal | smallest_subnormal | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| float16 | 10 | −14 | 2^(−14) ≈ 6.10e−5 | 2^(−24) ≈ 5.96e−8 | IEEE binary16 |
| float32 | 23 | −126 | 2^(−126) ≈ 1.18e−38 | 2^(−149) ≈ 1.40e−45 | IEEE binary32 |
| float128 | 63 (x86 80-bit ext) | −16382 | 2^(−16382) ≈ 3.36e−4932 | 2^(−16382 − 63) ≈ 4e−4951 | **Platform-extended**, not IEEE binary128 |

For each format, define:
- `ulp(x)` for x in normal binade `[2^k, 2^(k+1))`: `2^(k − mantissa_bits)`
- `ulp(subnormal)` = smallest_subnormal value (uniform spacing in subnormal range)

