## 3. The proof's format-agnosticism (FROZEN as audited claim)

The unified BACL proof:

> 1. Every positive float `x` is `N · ulp(x)` for integer N (precision-dependent N range, but always integer).
> 2. If `ulp(a) ≥ ulp(b)`, both are powers of 2 with `ulp(a)/ulp(b)` a non-negative integer power of 2.
> 3. So `a = N_a · ulp(a) = N_a · (ulp(a)/ulp(b)) · ulp(b)` — integer multiple of `ulp(b)`.
> 4. `b = N_b · ulp(b)` — integer multiple of `ulp(b)`.
> 5. `a − b` is integer multiple of `ulp(b)`. ∎

Lines 1–5 use only integer arithmetic and the lattice structure of floats. **No format-specific parameter** enters the proof — only the value of `ulp` changes. Therefore the proof transfers to any binary floating-point format with the same lattice structure.

